summary: An Ordinance approving and confirming the assessment and assessment roll of Local Improvement District No. 2726 for the improvement of The East One-half (E 1/2) of Thirty-second Avenue Northwest, from West Seventy-fifth Street to West Eightieth Street, all in the City of Seattle, by grading, curbing and constructing concrete walks, together with all necessary crosswalks and providing for the necessary surface drainage, under Ordinance No. 32069 and levying and assessing the amounts thereof against the several lots, tracts, parcels of land and other property as shown on said roll, establishing a Local Improvement Fund.
